cord\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":94005,\"bb\":93532,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93532/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eyas tu sarvāṇi bhūtāny\u003cbr /\u003eātmany evānupaśyati\u003cbr /\u003esarva-bhūteṣu cātmānaṁ\u003cbr /\u003etato na vijugupsate\u003c/em\u003e\"}]},{\"section\":\"synonyms\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.synonyms\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"books.Synonyms\",\"title\":\"synonyms\",\"id\":94006,\"bb\":93533,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93533/\",\"shadow_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eyaḥ\u003c/em\u003e – he who; \u003cem\u003etu\u003c/em\u003e – but; \u003cem\u003esarvāṇi\u003c/em\u003e – all; \u003cem\u003ebhūtāni\u003c/em\u003e – living entities; \u003cem\u003eātmani\u003c/em\u003e – in relation to the Supreme Lord; \u003cem\u003eeva\u003c/em\u003e – only; \u003cem\u003eanupaśyati\u003c/em\u003e – observes in a systematic way; \u003cem\u003esarva-bhūteṣu\u003c/em\u003e – in every living being; \u003cem\u003eca\u003c/em\u003e – and; \u003cem\u003eātmānam\u003c/em\u003e – the Supersoul; \u003cem\u003etataḥ\u003c/em\u003e – thereafter; \u003cem\u003ena\u003c/em\u003e – not; \u003cem\u003evijugupsate\u003c/em\u003e – hates anyone.\",\"word_for_word_value\":[{\"word\":\"yaḥ\",\"translation\":\"he who\"},{\"word\":\"tu\",\"translation\":\"but\"},{\"word\":\"sarvāṇi\",\"translation\":\"all\"},{\"word\":\"bhūtāni\",\"translation\":\"living entities\"},{\"word\":\"ātmani\",\"translation\":\"in relation to the Supreme Lord\"},{\"word\":\"eva\",\"translation\":\"only\"},{\"word\":\"anupaśyati\",\"translation\":\"observes in a systematic way\"},{\"word\":\"sarva-bhūteṣu\",\"translation\":\"in every living being\"},{\"word\":\"ca\",\"translation\":\"and\"},{\"word\":\"ātmānam\",\"translation\":\"the Supersoul\"},{\"word\":\"tataḥ\",\"translation\":\"thereafter\"},{\"word\":\"na\",\"translation\":\"not\"},{\"word\":\"vijugupsate\",\"translation\":\"hates anyone\"}]}]},{\"section\":\"translation\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.translation\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"translation\",\"id\":94007,\"bb\":93534,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93534/\",\"body_value\":\"He who systematically sees everything in relation to the Supreme Lord, who sees all living entities as His parts and parcels, and who sees the Supreme Lord within everything never hates anything or any being.\"}]},{\"section\":\"purport\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.purport\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94008,\"bb\":93535,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93535/\",\"body_value\":\"This is a description of the \u003cem\u003emahā-bhāgavata,\u003c/em\u003e the great personality who sees everything in relation to the Supreme Personality of Godhead. The Supreme Lord’s presence is realized in three stages. The \u003cem\u003ekaniṣṭha-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e is in the lowest stage of realization. He goes to a place of worship, such as a temple, church or mosque, according to his religious faith, and worships there according to scriptural injunctions. Devotees in this stage consider the Lord to be present at the place of worship and nowhere else. They cannot ascertain who is in what position in devotional service, nor can they tell who has realized the Supreme Lord. Such devotees follow the routine formulas and sometimes quarrel among themselves, considering one type of devotion better than another. These \u003cem\u003ekaniṣṭha-adhikārīs\u003c/em\u003e are actually materialistic devotees who are simply trying to transcend the material boundary to reach the spiritual plane.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94009,\"bb\":93536,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93536/\",\"body_value\":\"Those who have attained the second stage of realization are called \u003cem\u003emadhyama-adhikārīs.\u003c/em\u003e These devotees observe the distinctions between four categories of being: (1) the Supreme Lord; (2) the devotees of the Lord; (3) the innocent, who have no knowledge of the Lord; and (4) the atheists, who have no faith in the Lord and hate those in devotional service. The \u003cem\u003emadhyama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e behaves differently toward these four classes of person. He adores the Lord, considering Him the object of love; he makes friends with those who are in devotional service; he tries to awaken the dormant love of God in the hearts of the innocent; and he avoids the atheists, who deride the very name of the Lord.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94010,\"bb\":93537,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93537/\",\"body_value\":\"$3f\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94011,\"bb\":93538,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93538/\",\"body_value\":\"Those who imitate an \u003cem\u003euttama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e by flaunting a sense of oneness or fellowship but who behave on the bodily platform are actually false philanthropists. The conception of universal brotherhood must be learned from an \u003cem\u003euttama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e and not from a foolish person who does not properly understand the individual soul or the Supreme Lord’s Supersoul expansion, who dwells everywhere.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94012,\"bb\":93539,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93539/\",\"body_value\":\"$40\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94013,\"bb\":93540,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93540/\",\"body_value\":\"$41\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":94014,\"bb\":93541,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/6/b93541/\",\"body_value\":\"According to the \u003ca href=\\\"/en/library/bg/18/54/\\\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā\u003c/em\u003e (18.54)\u003c/a\u003e, only one who is already on the liberated platform (\u003cem\u003ebrahma-bhūta\u003c/em\u003e) can become an \u003cem\u003euttama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e devotee and see every living being as his own brother. This vision cannot be had by politicians, who are always after some material gain. One who imitates the symptoms of an \u003cem\u003euttama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e may serve another’s outward body for the purpose of fame or material reward, but he does not serve the spirit soul. Such an imitator can have no information of the spiritual world. The \u003cem\u003euttama-adhikārī\u003c/em\u003e sees the spirit soul within the material body and serves him as spirit. Thus the material aspect is automatically served.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Iso 6\",\"medium_title\":\"Śrī Īśopaniṣad 6\"},{\"id\":94015,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"7\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"Mantra Seven\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/advanced-view/#bb93542\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/am/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/da/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti keel (Estonian)\",\"language_code\":\"et\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/et/library/iso/7/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Suomen kieli (Finnish)\",\"language_code\":\"fi\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/fi/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Français (French)\",\"language_code\":\"fr\",\"enabled