e mind is the intelligence, and above the intelligence is the soul. Thus the aim of real education should be self-realization, realization of the spiritual values of the soul. Any education which does not lead to such realization must be considered \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"11\",{\"children\":\"avidyā,\"}],\" or nescience. And to culture such nescience means to go down to the darkest region of ignorance.\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94045\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:9:child_items:3:children:4\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"According to the \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"1\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (2.42, 7.15), mistaken mundane educators are known as \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"veda-vāda-rata\"}],\" and \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"māyayāpahṛta-jñāna.\"}],\" They may also be atheistic demons, the lowest of men. Those who are \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"veda-vāda-rata\"}],\" pose themselves as very learned in the Vedic literature, but unfortunately they are completely diverted from the purpose of the \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"9\",{\"children\":\"Vedas.\"}],\" In the \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"11\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/15/15/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (15.15)\"]}],\" it is said that the purpose of the \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"Vedas\"}],\" is to know the Personality of Godhead, but these \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"15\",{\"children\":\"veda-vāda-rata\"}],\" men are not at all interested in the Personality of Godhead. On the contrary, they are fascinated by such fruitive results as the attainment of heaven.\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94046\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:9:child_items:3:children:5\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:te