"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eparas tasmāt tu bhāvo ’nyo\u003cbr /\u003e’vyakto ’vyaktāt sanātanaḥ\u003cbr /\u003eyaḥ sa sarveṣu bhūteṣu\u003cbr /\u003enaśyatsu na vinaśyati\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94157\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:7\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"All the material planets – upper, lower and intermediate, including the sun, moon and Venus – are scattered throughout the universe. These planets exist only during the lifetime of Brahmā. Some lower planets, however, are vanquished after the end of one day of Brahmā and are again created during the next day of Brahmā. On the upper planets, time is calculated differently. One of our years is equal to only twenty-four hours, or one day and night, on many of the upper planets. The four ages of earth (Satya, Tretā, Dvāpara and Kali) last only twelve thousand years according to the time scale of the upper planets. Such a length of time multiplied by one thousand constitutes one day of Brahmā, and one night of Brahmā is the same. Such days and nights accumulate into months and years, and Brahmā lives for one hundred such years. At the end of Brahmā’s life, the complete universal manifestation is vanquished.\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94158\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:8\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$c8\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94159\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:9\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"The predominating Supreme Person residing within the spiritual nature is Lord Śrī Kṛṣṇa. As confirmed in the \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/8/22/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (8.22)\"]}],\", He can be approached only by unalloyed devotional service and not by the processes of \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"jñāna\"}],\" (philosophy), \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"yoga\"}],\" (mysticism) or \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"karma\"}],\" (fruitive work). The \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"9\",{\"children\":\"karmīs,\"}],\" or fruitive workers, can elevate themselves to the Svargaloka planets, which include the sun and the moon. \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"11\",{\"children\":\"Jñānīs\"}],\" and \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"yogīs\"}],\" can attain still higher planets, such as Maharloka, Tapoloka and Brahmaloka, and when they become still more qualified through devotional service they can enter into the spiritual nature, either the illuminating cosmic atmosphere of the spiritual sky (Brahman) or the Vaikuṇṭha planets, according to their qualification. It is certain, however, that no one can enter into the spiritual Vaikuṇṭha planets without being trained in devotional service.\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94160\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:10\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"On the material planets, everyone from Brahmā down to the ant is trying to lord it over material nature, and this is the material disease. As long as this material disease continues, the living entity has to undergo the process of bodily change. Whether he takes the form of a man, demigod or animal, he ultimately has to endure an unmanifested condition during the two devastations – the devastation during the night of Brahmā and the devastation at the end of Brahmā’s life. If we want to put an end to this process of repeated birth and death, as well as the concomitant factors of old age and disease, we must try to enter the spiritual planets, where we can live eternally in the association of Lord Kṛṣṇa or His plenary expansions, His Nārāyaṇa forms. Lord Kṛṣṇa or His plenary expansions dominate every one of these innumerable planets, a fact confirmed in the \u003cem\u003eśruti mantras: eko vaśī sarva-gaḥ kṛṣṇa īḍyaḥ/ eko ’pi san bahudhā yo ’vabhāti.\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eGopāla-tāpanī Upaniṣad\u003c/em\u003e 1.21)\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94161\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:11\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"No one can dominate Kṛṣṇa. It is the conditioned soul who tries to dominate material nature and is instead subjected to the laws of material nature and the sufferings of repeated birth and death. The Lord comes here to reestablish the principles of religion, and the basic principle is the development of an attitude of surrender to Him. This is the Lord’s last instruction in the \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/18/66/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (18.66)\"]}],\": \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"sarva-dharmān parityajya mām ekaṁ śaraṇaṁ vraja\"}],\". “Give up all other processes and just surrender unto Me alone.” Unfortunately, foolish men have misinterpreted this prime teaching and misled the masses of people in diverse ways. People have been urged to open hospitals but not to educate themselves to enter into the spiritual kingdom by devotional service. They have been taught to take interest only in temporary relief work, which can never bring real happiness to the living entity. They start varieties of public and semi-governmental institutions to tackle the devastating power of nature, but they don’t know how to pacify insurmountable nature. Many men are advertised as great scholars of the \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā,\"}],\" but they overlook the \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"Gītā’s\"}],\" message, by which material nature can be pacified. Powerful nature can be pacified only by the awakening of God consciousness, as clearly pointed out in the \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"9\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (7.14)\"]}],\".\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94162\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:12\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"In this \u003cem\u003emantra, Śrī Īśopaniṣad\u003c/em\u003e teaches that one must perfectly know both \u003cem\u003esambhūti\u003c/em\u003e (the Personality of Godhead) and \u003cem\u003evināśa\u003c/em\u003e (the temporary material manifestation), side by side. By knowing the material manifestation alone, one cannot be saved, for in the course of nature there is devastation at every moment (\u003cem\u003eahany ahani bhūtāni gacchantīha yamā-layam\u003c/em\u003e). Nor can one be saved from these devastations by the opening of hospitals. One can be saved only by complete knowledge of the eternal life of bliss and awareness. The whole Vedic scheme is meant to educate men in this art of attaining eternal life. People are often misguided by temporary attractive things based on sense gratification, but service rendered to the sense objects is both misleading and degrading.\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94163\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:14:child_items:3:children:13\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"We must therefore save ourselves and our fellow man in the right way. There is no question of liking or disliking the truth. It is there. If we want to be saved from repeated birth and death, we must take to the devotional service of the Lord. There can be no compromise, for this is a matter of necessity.\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"9f:[\"$\",\"div\",\"94164-verse_text,94164-verse_text\",{\"className\":\"av-verse_text\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4 hidden\",\"children\":\"Verse text\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94165\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:15:child_items:0:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003ehiraṇmayena pātreṇa\u003cbr /\u003esatyasyāpihitaṁ mukham\u003cbr /\u003etat tvaṁ pūṣann apāvṛṇu\u003cbr /\u003esatya-dharmāya dṛṣṭaye\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}]]]}]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"a0:[\"$\",\"div\",\"94164-synonyms,94164-synonyms\",{\"className\":\"av-synonyms\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Synonyms\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L62\",\"child-94166\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:15:child_items:1:children:0\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-justify\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"wfwundefined-0\",{\"className\":\"inline\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"wfwundefined-0-hiraṇmayena\",{\"href\":\"/en/sear